<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06158174 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06158174 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  UNION-CITY; MAN; JAIL; SENTENCE; SHOOTING; SHOPPING-CENTER  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  An Alameda County Superior Court judge has sentenced a 19-year-old Union Cityman to one year in county jail for shooting at a group of Newark youths andwounding a 15-year-old girl April 5 at the Lido Faire Shopping Center.;    Inaddition, Judge Stanley Golde on Tuesday ordered Thomas Cruz Duran to stayaway from gangs and any type of weapons. Duran, who had pleaded guilty toassault with a deadly weapon, also was ordered to pay a $100 fine and placedon three years' probation.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TEEN GETS 1-YEAR SENTENCE IN SHOOTING OFGIRL, 15  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Duran was given the maximum sentence allowed under terms of his pleabargain last month in Fremont-Newark-Union City Municipal Court.;    A14-year-old youth from Union City who also pleaded guilty, admitting he loadeda shotgun and fired it, was sentenced last month to a minimum term of eightmonths at Chabot Camp, a juvenile detention facility in San Leandro.;    LastApril, members of two area gangs -- Old Alvarado Boys from Union City andNewark XIV -- became involved in a confrontation at a carnival which spilledover to Newark's Lido Faire parking lot. There, Duran and another youth firedat a Toyota driven by the Newark youths, police said.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  SANDRA GONZALES, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Alameda County/AM  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910606  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  202  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday June 6, 199100158174,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>